ions alive.} 7. Nf3 b5 8. Ba2 {At least from here the bishop doesn't bother any other pieces.} Bb7 9. O-O Nbd7 {We are probably at the most important position of the 4.a3 line. White has tried several moves; a few of them are interesting, and Black should be careful.} 10. e4 {Almost a new move, but quite interesting! I wouldn't recommend accepting the gift because the opening of the e-file with d4 - d5 , and Re1 at some point, comes fast.} cxd4 (10... Nxe4 $6 {would be inaccurate due to the following sequence:} 11. Nxe4 Bxe4 12. Ng5 $1 {Suddenly, there are several threats, especially toward f7 and e6 .} Bb7 13. d5 e5 14. Re1 c4 15. b3 $1 Be7 16. bxc4 {( h4 instead is also interesting.)} Bxg5 17. c5 {and the engine seems to see very nice compensations for White.}) 11. Nxd4 {The threat e4 - e5 is prevented, and Black can continue development.} Bc5 12. Be3 O-O 13. Nxe6 {The engine suggestion, to keep equality.} fxe6 14. e5 {Quite a hidden idea!} Bxe3 15. exf6 Bxf2+ 16. Rxf2 Rxf6 17. Rxf6 Nxf6 18. Bxe6+ Kf8 {And the endgame is equal.} *

