ions alive.} 7. Nf3 b5 8. Ba2 {At least from here the bishop doesn't bother any other pieces.} Bb7 9. O-O Nbd7 {We are probably at the most important position of the 4.a3 line. White has tried several moves; a few of them are interesting, and Black should be careful.} 10. Re1 {White has a good score with this move.} Be7 {We can continue development without fearing e4 .} 11. e4 cxd4 12. Nxd4 Ne5 {Black absolutely needs to know this move to stay in the game. Otherwise, e5 would be a nasty move.} 13. Bf4 Ng6 14. Bg3 O-O 15. e5 Nh5 ({We are leaving the last 4 games which all saw} 15... Nd5 {. Instead, Black offers a knight trade.}) 16. Qxh5 Qxd4 17. Rad1 Qc5 {White seems to be out of good plans, and Black will quickly bring the rooks into play. The bishops on a2 and g3 are clearly weak.} *

