. Nc3 Nc6 10. Qd1 Rd8 {, when the material gain won't compensate for White's suffering.}) 8... Nc6 9. Qd3 {It's probably slightly better than the Qxd4 variation, but it's not enough for White.} Qb6 10. Bg2 d4 11. Ne4 Be7 12. O-O O-O {And both rooks are quickly coming into play.} *

