and I prefer to avoid that.}) 7. Nxd4 Nbd7 {The threat is now to gain a piece with ... e5 .} 8. Bg3 {It's never very nice to have to lose a full tempo in the opening like this.} Bb4 9. Bxc4 Ne4 10. Qc2 Bxc3+ 11. bxc3 Nxg3 12. hxg3 Nf6 {Of course, we couldn't castle already due to the mate on h7 . However, the position isn't dangerous for Black, who will most probably wait for White to castle first. In the meantime, we can develop the queenside and remain with a better pawn structure.} *

