and I prefer to avoid that.}) 7. Qxd4 Qxd4 8. Nxd4 {White is hoping that better development can bring something. But that's not clear how exactly! Now, Black has at least a couple of good options, and the choice will depend on your style.} Nbd7 {The risky choice!} 9. Ndb5 e5 {The right reaction! Black attacks the bishop and shouldn't be afraid of the fork.} 10. Nc7+ Kd8 11. Nxa8 {I would say this position is quite unlikely to happen, but as it's critical according to the engine, I will add a few ideas.} exf4 {Right now, Black is an exchange down for a pawn, but with decent chances to catch the knight on a8 , or at least to make it a hard task to escape.} 12. exf4 b5 {Black sacrifices the b-pawn to accelerate development.} 13. Nxb5 Bb4+ 14. Kd1 Ng4 {White is in trouble already.} *

