and I prefer to avoid that.}) 7. Qxd4 Qxd4 8. Nxd4 {White is hoping that better development can bring something. But that's not clear how exactly! Now, Black has at least a couple of good options, and the choice will depend on your style.} Nbd7 {The risky choice!} 9. Ndb5 e5 {The right reaction! Black attacks the bishop and shouldn't be afraid of the fork.} 10. Nc7+ Kd8 11. Nxa8 {I would say this position is quite unlikely to happen, but as it's critical according to the engine, I will add a few ideas.} exf4 {Right now, Black is an exchange down for a pawn, but with decent chances to catch the knight on a8 , or at least to make it a hard task to escape.} 12. Bxc4 fxe3 13. fxe3 Bd6 {Black covers the c7 -square and prepares to get the rook into the game.} 14. O-O-O Ke7 15. Rxd6 {With this decision, the knight escapes safely, but the pawn structure will be in Black's favor.} Kxd6 16. Rd1+ Ke7 17. Nc7 Ne5 {The position is complicated. Black has the better pawn structure, but White has active pieces right now. Chances are balanced.} *

