ne. It can also happen via other move orders, such as Nc3 Nf6} 5. Nf3 {Be7 Bg5 . We are going to deeply analyze this line, and it's also important to understand that it can often transpose into the lines with e3 . And when a transposition occurs, we will have a look at it via 5.e3 .}) 5... h6 ({Similarly to a latter chapter, I like to start immediately with ...h6 . I would say it's slightly more accurate to do it straight away, at least Black knows exactly how White will react to the attack. If you compare with} 5... O-O {, Black doesn't show the place of the king immediately.}) {Also, let's mention that there is no real need to analyze Bf4 , it's just a transposition to the chapter on Bf4 , with ... h6 already played, and that's a better version for Black. Black can play similarly.} 6. Bh4 {There is no need to argue, this is the main line for White, who doesn't want to release the pressure.} O-O {Now, in case of the usual e3 , this is a transposition into the other main line, starting with 5.e3 . So we will only look at secondary possibilities.} 7. cxd5 {White can also decide to take now on d5 . As usual, when this happens so late, Black can take back with the knight to simplify the position.} Nxd5 8. Bxe7 Qxe7 ({Now, once again, Nxd5 exd5 e3} 8... b6 {can lead to the main line of the chapter, but Black also has other options than b6 now that is already free to develop the light-squared bishop. Instead, we will look at some of White's other options.}) 9. e3 {That's a bit slow for White.} Nxc3 10. bxc3 b6 11. Bd3 Bb7 {The bishop has reached a dominant position. Now, ... c5 will come.} 12. O-O c5 13. Qe2 Nc6 {There are not so many plans for White. It's hard to ever push e4 , as ... Rad8 would attack the d4 -pawn and it's hard to protect it. Maybe trading pieces to achieve a draw is the best idea.} 14. Be4 Rac8 15. Rfc1 Na5 {The knight could use the c4 -square.} 16. Bxb7 Qxb7 {Black is very slightly better as in 0-1 Georgiev-Azarov, Dayton 2017. Black will try to double the rooks on the c-file before threatening to take on d4 , to win the battle of c-file. To see how to win this kind of position, check the Model Games section!} *

