l move too, to develop and castle. It seems more logical to me than} 12. Be2 {, which is less active.}) 12... c5 13. dxc5 {White forces the hanging pair of pawns in the center before ... c4 can be played.} bxc5 14. O-O Nd7 {The most logical square for the knight. It simply protects the c5 -pawn.} 15. e4 {A concrete approach, and the main move in the position.} d4 {Of course. Taking on e4 would leave a very weak pawn on c5 .} 16. Bb1 Bg4 {Bringing the bishop to the kingside is a nice idea.} 17. h3 Bh5 18. Qd3 {Thanks to the bishop on h5 , there is no real threat of e4 - e5 .} Rac8 19. Nd2 {White is intending f4 .} Ne5 20. Qg3 Qg5 {White has completely blocked Black's pawns but lacks space, so the endgame is slightly in Black's favor.} *

