astling, but we can't say it's long-term.} Bf8 ({I think that's my preference over the other option:} 11... Ng4 {. The reason is that when Black plays ... Ng4 , the only option for the knight later on is to go back to f6 , while the bishop can choose between e7 , d6 , g7 , and even b4 -squares.}) 12. Bf4 Bg7 13. Bd6 {The bishop is unable to stay on the a3 - f8 diagonal to prevent Black from castling.} Nb6 14. Bc5 Nfd7 15. Ba3 Nc4 {The bishop on a3 won't stay on the diagonal for very long, it will get traded, so Black is fine.} *

