te has tried many moves. Obviously, the minority attack is the main plan for White, but we will also have a look at a couple of other options.} 12. h3 {This provides a square for the bishop to go back to f4 and h2 .} Re8 13. Bf4 ({This position has been reached from} 13. Bf4 {c6 Qc2 with White to move. Let's try to make use of this extra tempo.}) 13... Nb6 {I think this already discourages White from going for a minority attack because of the c4 -square.} 14. Ne5 Nfd7 15. Nf3 Nf8 {Black isn't satisfied with a draw and tries to improve the pieces.} 16. Rab1 a5 17. Rfe1 Ne6 18. Be5 Nc4 {White lacks a real plan. Even if it's not easy to do something useful with Black as well, I would still pick Black's side. ½-½ Vescovi-Tin, Sharjah UAE 2023. Probably the next step would be to try to trade the dark-squared bishops with ... Bd6 .} *

