te has tried many moves. Obviously, the minority attack is the main plan for White, but we will also have a look at a couple of other options.} 12. Rab1 a5 13. Qc2 ({With this move order, White avoids the option of} 13. a3 a4 {.}) 13... Re8 14. a3 Nh5 {Black simplifies the position and immediately gets rid of the bishop.} 15. Bxe7 Qxe7 16. b4 {If White wants this move to work, White shouldn't wait any longer.} axb4 17. axb4 b5 {I like this straightforward continuation. If allowed, the next two moves are ... Nb6 - c4 closing the c-file forever.} 18. Rfe1 {Here, I would improve over the game ½-½ Vazquez Igarza-Moreno Trujillo, Linares 2013, by bringing the knight into play to avoid a strong 19.e4 .} Nhf6 19. Nd2 Nb6 20. e4 dxe4 21. Ncxe4 Nxe4 22. Nxe4 Rac8 {Now that e4 has been played, the knight's dream square is more d5 than c4 , to attack b4 . So we start by protecting c6 , Black is in control.} *

