on the queenside, as the black pieces are coming} 13. Nd2 a4 14. a3 b5 15. Na2 {And here, in the game 0-1 Schenderowitsch-Demuth, Germany 2016, I kept an advantage with Nb6 , but apparently, it was stronger to castle first.} O-O-O 16. e3 Be7 17. Be2 Kb7 {That's the point: the c6 -pawn is well-protected, and there will always be time to bring the knight to b6 and c4 .} *

