ly playable, coming forth with different modern ideas.  It's time to examine these plans, but first, we will focus on the sidelines for White on move 5!}) 4... exd5 {As I just said, we accept to enter the theory of the Orthodox Queen's Gambit. It may seem that it will be a simple task to develop the c8 -bishop, but actually, that's only partially true. Whenever it develops, we should be careful about Qb3 , attacking both b7 and d5 . But also, Qc2 or Bd3 are coming fast to prevent ... Bf5 , and ... Bg4 can be easily repelled by means of f3 .} 5. Bg5 {This is the classical continuation in the Exchange Variation of the Queen's Gambit Declined. The goal is to put some pressure on the d5 -pawn. White is usually intending to follow with 6.e3 and 7.Bd3 to avoid the development of the bishop to f5 .} c6 {Black starts by securing the d5 -pawn. Now that we have prevented the threat Bxf6 Qxf6 Nxd5 , the idea is to develop the c8 -bishop. But it's not clear if we will be able to manage this!} 6. Qc2 {This directly prevents ... Bf5 .} h6 {As against e3 , we start with this move, forcing White to decide what to do with the bishop.} 7. Bh4 Be6 {This idea is simply to develop the bishop first, before bringing the knight to d7 .} (7... g6 {would be in the spirit of our analysis in the previous chapter, managing ... Bf5 . But to see something different and very interesting here, I would like to show a completely different setup.}) 8. e3 Nbd7 9. Bd3 {This looks like the most flexible move, but it allows Black to gain the bishop pair.} g5 {The right decision. Black chases the bishop away and will try to trade it.} 10. Bg3 Nh5 {Black immediately challenges the bishop, which can't escape.} 11. Nge2 Nxg3 12. Nxg3 h5 {I already like Black's position here. We have several options, but the idea, in general, is to push ... h4 , and after Nf5 , to attack the knight with ... Qf6 . I don't think it's necessary to know more by heart, but I decided to analyze this position in the Model Games section: 0-1 Rodshtein-Santos Latasa, Krakow 2023.} *

