t to get the pawn on h7 hanging (to the bishop on d3 ). Now, normally the bishop goes back to h4 , but we have to consider the other options.} 7. Bh4 {White keeps the pin.} Be7 {Now that f6 is protected, Black can play ... Bf5 without fearing Qf3 , destroying the pawn structure.} 8. Bd3 {The most logical move order, preventing ... Bf5 .} (8. Qc2 {also prevents ... Bf5 but it has no independent value.} O-O {and now White's only options are} 9. Bd3 {, which is a direct transposition to Bd3 O-O Qc2 , while Nf3} Ne4 {works too, and after} 10. Bxe7 Qxe7 {Bd3 , we are in a variation we cover in Bd3 O-O} 11. Nf3 {.}) (8. Nf3 $6 Bf5 $1 {There is no reason to refrain from this move. After} 9. Bd3 Bxd3 10. Qxd3 Nbd7 {, we transposed back into the 8.e3 variation .}) 8... O-O {For now, Black has kept many options concerning the knight on b8 and the bishop on c8 . Now, White has several different choices. It's usually at this moment that White needs to show which plan is on the agenda.  The two main plans are Nge2 , with f3 and e4 at some point, when play is directed at the center, and the other plan is Nf3 connected to Rb1 , b4 - b5 , called the minority attack, to create a weakness on the queenside (we have seen this plan several times already).} 9. Nf3 ({As against} 9. h3 {, we can get the knight to e4 since Nf3 doesn't prevent it at all.}) 9... Ne4 {Even if the knight is hanging there, the fact that White first needs to take on e7 saves the day.} 10. Bg3 {To my eyes, White should take the bishop instead of allowing us to trade it for a knight.} Nxg3 11. hxg3 {Giving the bishop pair this easily is rarely good. I think the only justification is to castle on the queenside and attack on the kingside.} Nd7 12. Qc2 Nf6 13. O-O-O Bd6 14. Kb1 Re8 {I don't see a clear path for White to organize an attack. Black has centralized the pieces and will start the attack with ... b5 and ... a5 .} 15. Nh4 b5 {A logical new move, to start the attack on the white king.} 16. Nf5 Bf8 {There was probably no threat yet on h6 , but we also prefer to keep the bishop. Both f3 and g4 are not playable right now, and the attack feels slow for White.} *

