hen we can take on a5 , but even more accurate is Nd6 to prevent White's e4 . The a5 -pawn is not going anywhere and can be captured next. If White insists on trying to get counterplay with f3 , after} f5 {, the pawn on e3 will also be a target in the long run, and Black is slightly better.}) *

