ssible here, as it's not protected enough.}) 10. Bg3 Nd6 11. Nf3 ({I don't feel this is the best try, but instead,} 11. Nge2 {is analyzed via 9.Nge2 .}) 11... Be6 12. O-O Nd7 {I tried a few different plans for White, but without much success.} 13. Ne2 {The knight heads towards f4 .} Nf6 14. Ne5 {White frees the f3 -square for the pawn.} Qc8 {Black prepares ... Bf5 .} 15. f3 Re8 16. Rae1 Bf5 17. Nc3 Bxd3 18. Qxd3 Bd8 {The bishop heads towards b6 to attack the d4 -pawn.} 19. e4 Bb6 {Again, the knight on e5 is clumsy, and in the meantime, the center is under pressure too.} *

