Nd6 {Black has managed to get rid of the light-squared bishop and now needs to develop, to prevent White's possibilities to play e4 or b4 - b5 .} 14. b4 a5 {Right now, b5 isn't really playable. We try to weaken White's queenside.} 15. a3 Na6 16. Qb3 {Protecting b4 , but it doesn't prevent our plan to get to the c4 -square.} axb4 17. axb4 Nc7 {Black quickly wants to play ... b5 and invade on c4 with the knight. The weakness of the c6 -pawn doesn't count as long as we have a knight on c4 .} *

