 b4 Nd7 14. b5 Nb6 {The knight heads towards c4 , and Black is fine having a weak pawn on c6 .} 15. bxc6 bxc6 16. Na4 {The knight tries to reach c5 , and it's okay to trade it.} Nbc4 17. e4 {White uses the fact that the knight is hanging on c4 , but we have an intermediate move.} Na3 {Black chases the queen away, in order to take on e4 .} 18. Qxc6 dxe4 {If White takes on Qxa8 , then exd3 attacks the knight on e2 and threatens ... Bb7 .} 19. Bxe4 Bb7 20. Qxd6 Bxe4 21. f3 {Not the best way to prevent the mate, as it also weakens the diagonal in front of the king.} Nc2 {The knight escapes and attacks the rook on a1 .} 22. fxe4 Qe3+ 23. Kh1 Nxa1 {White doesn't have enough material.} *

