 b4 Nd7 14. b5 Nb6 {The knight heads towards c4 , and Black is fine having a weak pawn on c6 .} 15. bxc6 bxc6 16. Na4 {The knight tries to reach c5 , and it's okay to trade it.} Nbc4 17. e4 {White uses the fact that the knight is hanging on c4 , but we have an intermediate move.} Na3 {Black chases the queen away, in order to take on e4 .} 18. Qxc6 dxe4 {If White takes on Qxa8 , then exd3 attacks the knight on e2 and threatens ... Bb7 .} 19. Bxe4 Bb7 20. Qxd6 Bxe4 21. Ng3 Nb5 ({In case of Qd7 , then} 21... Bd3 {holds everything. Black plays as an equilibrist!}) 22. Nxe4 Nxd6 23. Nxg5 hxg5 24. Rfd1 Rab8 {Black is a pawn down, but I just feel the draw should be decently easy to achieve, as Black can develop activity on the queenside. The knight on d6 is perfectly placed.} *

