 start with this logical move, keeping every option open, and having the possibility to attack the e3 -pawn in case of f2 - f3 .} 12. O-O {The bishop on g3 doesn't authorize White to castle queenside, as the launch of the pawns is difficult.} Bf8 {Again, directed against the e3 -pawn. Now, White has tried several options.} 13. Nf4 a5 14. Rfe1 {White slowly prepares f3 followed by e4 .} Na6 {Threatening ... Nb4 .} 15. a3 Nc7 16. Na4 Ne6 17. Nxe6 Bxe6 18. Nc5 {Now, in the game ½-½ Matlakov-Urazayev, Aktobe 2023, I think Black should have slowly gotten rid of the knight on c5 .} Bc8 {Black secures everything and wants to continue with ... b6 .} 19. Rac1 b6 20. Na4 Bd7 {Among the possible plans, Black can organize ... b5 and ... a4 to secure the c4 -square for the knight.} *

