 start with this logical move, keeping every option open, and having the possibility to attack the e3 -pawn in case of f2 - f3 .} 12. O-O {The bishop on g3 doesn't authorize White to castle queenside, as the launch of the pawns is difficult.} Bf8 {Again, directed against the e3 -pawn. Now, White has tried several options.} 13. b4 {With this move, White avoids ... a5 and immediately starts a minority attack.} Nd7 14. b5 Nb6 {Black clearly heads towards c4 with the knights.} 15. bxc6 bxc6 16. Na4 {The knight heads towards c5 . That's why, in the game 0-1 Abdisalimov-Sargissian, Tashkent 2023, I would rather take it immediately.} Nxa4 {At least here, no knight will get to c5 .} 17. Qxa4 Bd7 18. Qa6 Qb6 {Black keeps a very solid position and he will try to quickly take possession of the b-file if possible (even when White will have a rook on b1 , playing ... Rb6 would enable Black to double rooks or restore a good pawn structure if White takes it.} *


