1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 {The Queen's Gambit Declined! The very early stage of one of the oldest theoretical debates in chess. In this course, I am going to provide you with a full repertoire starting from this position.} ({Obviously Nc3 and Nf3 are the two main continuations. There are no independent tries here. e3 will transpose into the chapter on the Colle System. g3 is a rare move order to reach the Catalan Variation. Finally, a3 and Bf4 are extremely rare, and we will see similar lines after Nc3} 2... Nf6 {.}) 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. Bg5 {At first sight, it's not easy to understand why White would delay the development of the b1 -knight (as the idea isn't to place it on d2 , where it would be passive).} ({The majority of the games that reach this position are from the move order d4 Nf6 c4 e6 Nf3} 4. cxd5 {, where White wanted to avoid the Nimzo-Indian Defense (by playing 3.Nf3 ). And now Nc3 allows so many systems for Black as we already discussed.}) {So, by pinning the knight on g5 , White wants to provoke Be7 to transpose into the Queen's Gambit Declined. But Black also has different options here.} 4... dxc4 {That's my preference. Black immediately dares the opponent to get the pawn back, but Black may be willing to hold it!} 5. e3 {That's a little bit too shy for White, trying to attack the pawn, but it doesn't take possession of the center.} b5 {Of course, we should hold it here.} 6. Nc3 a6 {Black tries to avoid playing ... c5 . If we can manage ... c5 in one move, this is an improvement. But White can force matters.} 7. a4 c6 {Black protects the b5 -pawn, which is very logical.} 8. axb5 cxb5 9. Bxf6 gxf6 {We already mentioned why ... Qxf6 is bad (the Queen needs to protect the knight on b8 ).} 10. Nxb5 axb5 {Of course, here too, Black is glad to sacrifice the exchange to activate the bishops fast.} 11. Rxa8 Bb4+ 12. Nd2 Bb7 ({Black develops fast and chases the white rook away. In case of Ra7} 12... Qb6 {is good for Black.}) 13. Ra1 e5 {With a powerful development, Black is glad to open the center.} 14. Qh5 O-O {There is no reason to fear something around the King.} 15. Be2 exd4 {The complications appearing in the game 0-1 Gareyev-Nyzhnyk, Orlando 2019 will be analyzed in the Model Games section.} *

