1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 {The Queen's Gambit Declined! The very early stage of one of the oldest theoretical debates in chess. In this course, I am going to provide you with a full repertoire starting from this position.} ({Obviously Nc3 and Nf3 are the two main continuations. There are no independent tries here. e3 will transpose into the chapter on the Colle System. g3 is a rare move order to reach the Catalan Variation. Finally, a3 and Bf4 are extremely rare, and we will see similar lines after Nc3} 2... Nf6 {.}) 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. Bg5 {At first sight, it's not easy to understand why White would delay the development of the b1 -knight (as the idea isn't to place it on d2 , where it would be passive).} ({The majority of the games that reach this position are from the move order d4 Nf6 c4 e6 Nf3} 4. cxd5 {, where White wanted to avoid the Nimzo-Indian Defense (by playing 3.Nf3 ). And now Nc3 allows so many systems for Black as we already discussed.}) {So, by pinning the knight on g5 , White wants to provoke Be7 to transpose into the Queen's Gambit Declined. But Black also has different options here.} 4... dxc4 {That's my preference. Black immediately dares the opponent to get the pawn back, but Black may be willing to hold it!} 5. Qa4+ {White decides to attack the c4 -pawn immediately. Black has different ways to continue.} Nbd7 {With this move, Black also prepares ... c5 .} 6. e3 Be7 7. Bxc4 {It's not very logical to take back with the bishop when the Queen went to a4 . But at least, it enables White to avoid ... b5 .} O-O {White has to retreat a piece to avoid ... Nb6 with a fork.} 8. Be2 h6 {It can't be bad for Black to include this move. The bishop should decide where to go immediately.} 9. Bh4 c5 {In the end, Black reacts in the center.} 10. Nc3 a6 {As usual, Black also wants to bring the pawn to b5 to develop with ... Bb7 fast.} 11. O-O b5 {White can't touch this pawn using the pin, otherwise, ... Nb6 is a nasty intermediate move that protects a8 and gains the piece.} 12. Qc2 Bb7 {Black clearly has the more active position already.} *

