e pawn on e5 is under attack.} 14. Qe4 {And now we have an improvement over the game 0-1 Indjic-Yuan, chess.com.} Rd8 15. O-O Nc5 {Black trades the active d4 -rook.} 16. Rxd8+ Qxd8 17. Qe2 Bd7 {Once development is completed, Black has no weakness and a better position thanks to the bishop pair.} *

