 these super-aggressive systems, I often think that quick and sound development is the best reply. So let's just castle for now, there is no reason to be too scared of g4 and to organize a long castle or not castle at all.} 6. Qc2 {The second most played move but a serious mistake. It is slow and sometimes the Queen is exposed here.} dxc4 {Finally, we can take the hanging pawn; it frees the d5 -square for the knight too.} 7. e4 b5 {Black reacts in the center here as well. It will simplify the development of the Queenside.} 8. g5 Nfd7 9. Nxb5 c5 {Directly at the center!} 10. Bxc4 a6 11. Nc3 cxd4 12. Nxd4 Ne5 {White's position is already close to collapsing.} 13. Nce2 Bb7 {It's very unclear to me how White will find a safe place for the King.} *

