layed Nc3 instead of castling helps our position (as we will see when White has to take back on d1 and won't be able to do it with the rook).} {Now, I checked 3 different options for White: to recapture with the Queen, Qa4 , to recapture with the knight, Ne5 , which is a well-known theoretical move as well in the same position with O-O instead of Nc3 , and to castle immediately.} 7. Ne5 {In the same position with O-O instead of Nc3 , Black has to play Nc6 to try to equalize, while c5 is well-known to bring a safe advantage for White. But here, things are different!} c5 {I think that's the right decision, to directly fight in the center. As I said, in the same position with O-O instead of Nc3 , that's not a great move. But here the difference is that White won't be able to take back with the rook on d1 .} 8. dxc5 {Even if White is not able to take back on d1 with the rook, that's the right move. White will try to prove a slight edge in a symmetrical position (thanks to the strong bishop on g2 ), but I don't feel it's a realistic goal.} Qxd1+ 9. Nxd1 Bxc5 {White always has many different ways to play these positions but is usually not in a rush to take back on c4 .} 10. O-O Nd5 ({Instead,} 10... Nc6 {is also a possibility, but I prefer a central approach, not having weak pawns on the Queenside.}) 11. Ne3 {White voluntarily allows us to damage the pawn structure to get rid of Black's two active pieces.} Nxe3 12. Bxe3 Bxe3 13. fxe3 c3 {Black wants to leave the opponent with the most stupid pawn structure possible.} 14. bxc3 f6 15. Nd3 Rf7 {I like this precise move. Black immediately protects b7 and is ready to develop the Queenside.} 16. Rad1 Nc6 {I don't think taKing on c6 and bringing the knight to c5 will provide White with enough play as shown in the following variation.} 17. c4 {The game ½-½ Sevian-Lazavik, chess.com 2023, continued with Na5 , but we will deviate.} Re7 18. Bxc6 bxc6 19. Nc5 Re8 20. Rd3 e5 21. Kf2 Bg4 {Black brings the bishop back to g6 or f7 . The fact that c4 is sometimes hanging is a problem for White.} *

