but the knight is out of play.} b6 8. cxb6 axb6 9. b3 Bb7 10. e3 {White tries to finish development, but Black won't contribute by taKing and will develop even faster.} Nc6 11. a3 O-O 12. Be2 Ng4 {A nice continuation. Black threatens to take on e3 to damage the pawn structure, so White should chase the knight.} 13. h3 Nge5 14. Nxe5 Nxe5 {But now, there are even more threats.} 15. exd4 {The right move, to avoid ... d3 .} Bxg2 16. Rg1 Nf3+ 17. Bxf3 Bxf3 {The game is extremely tense. Black seems to enjoy full compensation for the pawn because of the long-term problem for White to get the King to a safe spot.} *

