d it prevents Qc2 .} 7. Qb3 {When the bishop leaves the c8 -square early, that's always a move we should consider. But here, Black has a thematic sacrifice.} Nc6 {The knight threatens to come to b4 , with deadly threats on c2 .} 8. Qxb7 {The critical move.} Nb4 9. Rc1 {The Queen isn't in danger on b7 since the c7 -pawn is hanging.} O-O 10. Qxc7 Qxc7 11. Bxc7 Rfc8 12. Bf4 Ne4 {Black is two pawns down but has good chances to get one back on the Queenside, and White cannot castle easily.} *

