retreat to h4 , transposing to a position we have already seen, and the rest is not very dangerous.} (7... Bf5 {is also possible. White will most probably transpose to similar positions but also has a few extra options.} 8. Nh4 $5 {is one of the possible attempts for White. Here, ... Bh7 isn't allowed (in contrast to the 7...h6  Bh4 variation), and White can try to exploit the f5 -square. (Instead, after} Bd3 9. Bxd3 {Qxd3 , there is nothing new compared to our analysis.) Be6 Bd3 Black is still fine obviously, but things are less clear than after} h6 {.}) 8. Bxf6 {I don't think this offers White anything. Giving up the bishop pair so early should ease us to get a comfortable position.} Bxf6 9. Bd3 {At least, White has managed to prevent ... Bf5 .} (9. b4 {is met with} Be7 10. Qb3 Bf5 {and Black enjoys a fine development by having prevented Bd3 . Also, the minority attack isn’t that scary here. Note that after} 11. a3 b5 {, Black stops it while} 12. a4 {isn’t permitted, and we will continue with ... a5 or ... Nd7 - b6 .}) 9... O-O 10. O-O ({The most common move. As against} 10. h3 {, I like Black's prospects when we try to fight directly in the center.}) 10... c5 {It's also completely possible to play other classical plans, but this could reach equality by force.} 11. dxc5 Bxc3 {Again, it's important to destroy White's pawn structure and to prevent Nxd5 .} 12. bxc3 Nd7 13. c6 ({The rest is similar to the line after} 13. h3 {, and the position is balanced.}) 13... bxc6 14. c4 {White tries to get rid of the only weakness so that Black will remain with the isolated c-pawn.} dxc4 {The right decision. The isolated pawn on c6 is a lesser evil than the one on d5 , as White doesn't get the d4 -square for the knight.} 15. Bxc4 Qe7 16. Rc1 c5 {The pawn is meant to get there anyway, to prevent Nd4 . It also opens the long diagonal for the bishop.} 17. Bb5 Rb8 18. Qa4 Ne5 {That's a kind of dynamic equality. White can try to develop some pressure on the c5 -pawn, but while doing so, the King will feel lonely on g1 , and Black can develop some quick counterattack. Stockfish assesses this position as equal, and I do think White doesn't have enough to hope for something real here.} *

