stling.} b6 {I had to face this move some years ago when it wasn't popular at all and I couldn't get any advantage. Black is willing to develop similarly to the Tartakower line. The main move for White is to take immediately on d5 , but there are again some alternatives that we need to check now.} (6... Nbd7 {together with} 7. c5 {are the two main moves for Black. But I like the flexibility of our chosen line, which is also more in the spirit of the rest of our repertoire.}) 7. cxd5 {By taKing immediately, White forces us to show how we aim to take back: with a piece, to keep a safe pawn structure, or with a pawn, condemning ourselves to end up in a position with hanging pair of pawns whenever we will push ... c5 ?} Nxd5 {By far, with the knight! Black has just played ... b6 and doesn't want to close the diagonal so soon.} 8. Nxd5 {Same question as after cxd5 . This time the response is less clear, as it's good to have traded a pair of knights in the case of the hanging pawns, but I still prefer to go for the same idea to keep a safe pawn structure.} Qxd5 (8... exd5 {has been played just as often. This move lets the pawn on c7 unprotected, but it's a bit complicated to take it when White is so far from castling.}) 9. Bd3 {Developing the bishop is still the main move. White wants to castle next so let's try to prevent this.} Qa5+ {White obviously can't interpose the check with the Queen, so White has to move the King or retreat with the knight.} 10. Nd2 {The main move, but engines tend to think the position is already slightly preferable for Black!} Ba6 {Again, Black doesn't want to allow White to castle.} 11. Be4 {This is not going in the right direction. Black can sacrifice the exchange.} Nd7 {The goal for Black is to keep the amazing bishop on a6 . If White doesn't take on a8 , then 11.Be4 was stupid anyway, and Black can continue with ... Rc8 and ... b5 .} 12. Bxa8 Rxa8 13. a3 c5 14. b4 Qb5 15. f3 {White tries to find a way to develop, but the position is about to crack under Black's pressure.} Rd8 16. Kf2 cxd4 17. exd4 Qf5 18. Be3 Nf6 {White isn't safe at all; ... Ng4 + is coming, to get the bishop on e3 , and then have full control with the two bishops. Black is winning, from an engine point of view. Let's just say it's a very tough position for humans from White's perspective.} *

