Nc3} 6... Nc6 {, to occupy the center. Before analyzing the main line, we will see different sidelines for White.  We should mention something nice for Black: this line can be reached from different move orders. For instance, d4 Nf6 Nf3} 7. cxd5 {g3 e6 Bg2 Bd6 O-O O-O c4} h6 {, or via Réti move orders. That's an advantage in comparison with lines featuring dxc4 where Black has to look for different lines in the other move orders.}) 7. Nc3 ({Clearly, White's main line, and can also arise from different move orders. It wouldn't be a good idea for Black to continue with b6 , similarly to a line we have already seen because White would get an active position in the center (by} 7. Ne5 {Bb7 Bf4 , with nice pressure) and ideas with e4 coming.}) 7... Nc6 {Our whole system is based on this move. It may seem weird at first sight, and I was very surprised when I first faced it, as it's usually accepted that the knight is misplaced on c6 in the Queen's Gambit systems. But here, it fits Black's plan perfectly, as it can help us react in the center with ... e5 . It also restrains White's expansion on the Queenside when White wants c5 followed by b4 .} 8. Qd3 {I had to face this system as White against the strong French GM Etienne Bacrot during the French League 2023. I decided (after some thought because I didn't know this variation), to opt for this interesting move. I knew it probably wasn't the main option, but it was my goal to get something he might not know. Unfortunately, he replied quickly.} Nb4 {White's Queen needs to move again} 9. Qb1 {Again, I was seeKing an unusual square yet a playable one.} dxc4 10. Rd1 {White tries to prevent ... c5 .} Nfd5 {A strong move. The knight heads back towards b6 , to protect the c4 -pawn.} 11. Nd2 {Objectively not great, but logical, to take back on c4 .} Nb6 12. b3 {Unable to get my pawn back, I decided to offer a trade, to continue with e4 later, with interesting compensations in the center. Again, I like Bacrot's reaction.} N4d5 13. Nxd5 {0-1 Demuth-Bacrot, Chartres 2023.} Nxd5 {I think this possibility would have been even stronger, with the forKing threat on c3 .} 14. Qc2 cxb3 15. axb3 b6 {Black has secured the b4 -square for the knight. I prefer Black here.} *

