s not clear how White gets the pawn back.} dxc3 12. Qc2 Qxd6 13. Qxc3 Re8 {While parrying the threat of Ba3 , Black develops the rook, and White isn't even putting much pressure on the center, so there isn't enough for the pawn.} *

