comfortable position for Black with the strong bishop on e5 and the isolated c4 -pawn. Instead, White goes for the bishop chase.} Bxc5 {The only move in the position, the rest is bad for Black. Now, White can take any of the two pieces.} 12. dxc5 {White scored well in this line, but I still think Black's fine.} Qe7 {Black develops, leaves the d8 -square for a rook, and attacks the c5 -pawn.} 13. Nd5 Nxd5 14. Qxd5 {So far, White protects the c5 -pawn.} Rd8 15. Qe4 Qxc5 16. Be3 Qe7 17. Rfd1 Re8 {Once again, it's obvious that White has some compensation but can't dream of an advantage.} *

