s the c5 -square in Black's hands, and I believe it's a big concession.} Na5 {Already another issue for White: the c4 -pawn is exposed and not so easy to protect.} 11. c5 {I don't think this trade can be dangerous. White will have the central pawns, but Black also activates very quickly.} Bxc5 12. Nxe5 Re8 13. Nf3 Bf5 {It becomes hard for White to do anything in the center.} 14. Nd4 {To me, this is the start of a bad idea.} Bg6 15. e4 c6 {The knight on d4 is hanging, and the pawn on d5 is starting to feel feverish. Black has a very nice initiative.} *

