s the c5 -square in Black's hands, and I believe it's a big concession.} Na5 {Already another issue for White: the c4 -pawn is exposed and not so easy to protect.} 11. Nd2 {I wouldn't say it's a passive move, as it can help White to push in the center with e4 and f4 maybe at some point.} Bd7 {Black simply develops the remaining pieces. Now, ... c6 is in the air.} 12. Bb2 Re8 13. e4 {Apparently not a great move, but a very logical one.} c6 {Black immediately plays on the c-file.} 14. Qe2 Rc8 15. Rac1 Qb6 16. Ba1 Qa6 {The c4 -pawn, or the c4 -square in general, is in trouble. I don't see a plan for White, and Black will trade on d5 whenever it feels best. Black was already better in 0-1 Urazayev-Yoo, chess.com 2021.} *

