mmediate pressure on b7 , to prevent the development of the c8 -bishop.} exd4 {The best idea seems to trade immediately, to force matters.} 11. Nxd4 Nxd4 12. Qxd4 Re8 13. Rd1 Qe7 {These pass moves seemed very natural for both, to activate the pieces. Now, everyone has continued with Bb2 , placing the bishop on its nicest diagonal, but there is another interesting idea for White.} 14. Bxb7 {This direct approach isn't a good idea.} Bxb7 15. Rxb7 Be5 {Black will take on c3 and get the pawn back.} 16. Qe3 Bxc3 17. Qxc3 Qxe2 {White has a fragile position. There are ideas of ... Qxf2 + and the Kingside is not so well protected by White.} *

