1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Be7 {That's just another move order for White, but it can transpose back into our usual lines.} 4. Nf3 Nf6 5. Bg5 h6 6. Bh4 O-O 7. e3 b6 8. Bd3 Bb7 9. cxd5 Nxd5 10. Bxe7 Qxe7 11. O-O Nxc3 12. bxc3 c5 13. Qe2 Nc6 14. Be4 Rac8 15. Rfc1 Na5 16. Bxb7 Qxb7 {Until here, everything has been analyzed. Black has a slight advantage, thanks to the piece activity on the Queenside, but White is solid, and it's interesting to understand how Black can win such positions.} 17. Nd2 {White tries to keep control over the c4 -square.} Qd5 {If White does nothing, the plan is to double the rooks on the c-file and invade there after ... cxd4 . That's why, White decided to push immediately in the center.} 18. c4 Qd7 19. Nb3 cxd4 {That's the drawback of pushing c4 . Now, White needs to play with a hanging pair of pawns. Even if it can be dynamic sometimes, too many trades occurred already and the pawns are just weaknesses.} 20. exd4 (20. Nxa5 d3 21. Qd2 bxa5 22. Rc3 Rfd8) 20... Qa4 21. c5 {White decides to give a pawn to trade a few pieces.} ({After} 21. Nxa5 Qxa5 22. Rc2 Rfd8 23. Rd1 Qa4 {, there is a nice and long-term pressure on the pawns for Black.}) 21... Nxb3 22. axb3 Qxd4 23. Rxa7 ({To achieve a draw,} 23. Ra4 {would have been a better try.} Qd7 24. Rac4 bxc5 25. Rxc5 Rxc5 26. Rxc5 Rc8 27. Rxc8+ Qxc8 {and it's probably not winning yet for Black, but unpleasant to play for White.}) 23... Rxc5 24. Rxc5 Qxc5 {As the Queenside pawns are on the same file, it's harder to trade them, in comparison to the previous variation.} 25. g3 Qc1+ 26. Kg2 Qc6+ {This forces White to weaken the second rank.} 27. f3 (27. Qf3 $2 Qxf3+ 28. Kxf3 Rc8 29. Ra3 Rc3+ 30. Ke2 b5 31. Kd2 b4 {and Black gains another pawn.}) 27... Rd8 28. Ra2 Rd4 29. Rd2 e5 {Creating a passed d-pawn if White wants to trade rooks.} 30. Rxd4 exd4 31. Kf2 b5 32. Qe4 Qc5 33. Ke2 Qc3 34. Qe8+ Kh7 35. Qxf7 {Black has sacrificed this pawn because the d-pawn will promote.} d3+ 36. Kf1 (36. Ke3 d2+ 37. Ke2 Qc2 {and ... d1=Q with double check is unstoppable.}) 36... Qc1+ ({After Kf2} 36... Qc2 {Ke3 d2 , White has no check and the promotion is unstoppable.}) *

